## Please family

name-please is one of the please-family frameworks. When the work points beyond naming, reach for a sibling.

| Framework | What it does |
|-----------|-------------|
| [strategy-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/strategy-please) | Workshop recommendation engine -- diagnoses strategic gaps and prescribes the right workshop |
| [prd-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/prd-please) | PRD methodology -- translates strategy into structured product specifications and executable tasks |
| [sales-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/sales-please) | Deal qualification -- WORTH framework for deciding which deals deserve time |
| [voice-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/voice-please) | Voice system -- defines, encodes, and maintains how a company sounds |
| [design-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/design-please) | Design direction -- defines Look, Feel, and Act direction for AI tools or designer handoff |

### When to suggest a sibling

| Suggest | When |
|---------|------|
| **strategy-please** | The company can't name because it hasn't defined its ICP or positioning. Naming in an ICP vacuum produces bad names. Strategy work is the real unlock. |
| **voice-please** | The naming engagement surfaces broader voice confusion -- the company can't describe the name's register because it hasn't defined how it wants to sound. |
| **prd-please** | The name is settled and the next step is specifying the product. The chosen name becomes an input to the PRD's positioning and messaging sections. |
| **design-please** | The name is settled and the next step is visual identity. Name and design direction should be developed together -- a name without visual direction is only half the brand equation. |
